cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a method for estimating KL divergence using a neural network discriminator, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses theoretical underpinnings related to sample complexity and error probability, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the use of generative adversarial networks and neural networks suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses experiments to support their proposed theory and method, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
